  // Set 2
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'grammar','Which opening is most effective for a persuasive essay about school meals?',['A nutritious school meal is not a luxury — it is an investment in every child\'s future.','School meals are good and children eat them.','I think school meals might be important sometimes.','This essay is about school meals.'],'A nutritious school meal is not a luxury — it is an investment in every child\'s future.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'grammar','Which transition word is most persuasive when adding a strong point?',['Moreover','Also','And','Plus'],'Moreover',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'vocabulary','What does "compelling" mean?',['powerfully persuasive and convincing','very ordinary','slightly interesting','not very convincing'],'powerfully persuasive and convincing',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'vocabulary','What does "advocate" mean?',['to publicly support or recommend something','to argue against something','to remain neutral','to avoid a topic'],'to publicly support or recommend something',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'grammar','Which sentence uses a statistic to persuade?',['Research shows that students who eat breakfast score 20% higher in examinations.','Breakfast is a nice meal that some students eat.','Many students sometimes eat breakfast before school.','Breakfast might help students who are hungry.'],'Research shows that students who eat breakfast score 20% higher in examinations.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'vocabulary','What does "fundamental" mean?',['forming a necessary base; extremely important','slightly useful','not very important','completely optional'],'forming a necessary base; extremely important',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'grammar','Which is the best example of the "rule of three" in persuasive writing?',['Education develops minds, builds confidence, and transforms lives.','Education is good and useful.','Education is one important thing.','Education is something we all need.'],'Education develops minds, builds confidence, and transforms lives.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'vocabulary','What does hyperbole do in persuasive writing?',['It emphasises a point by overstating it for effect','It provides accurate statistical data','It presents a balanced argument','It defines a key term'],'It emphasises a point by overstating it for effect',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'grammar','Which sentence uses direct address persuasively?',['You, the reader, have the power to make this change happen today.','The reader can perhaps do something at some point.','Someone somewhere might make a change eventually.','Changes are possible for some people under certain conditions.'],'You, the reader, have the power to make this change happen today.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,2,'vocabulary','What does "consequence" mean in persuasive writing?',['the result of an action, often used to warn of negative outcomes','a type of evidence','an appeal to authority','a definition of a term'],'the result of an action, often used to warn of negative outcomes',term:2),

  // Set 3 — comprehension
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'comprehension','PASSAGE (PERSUASIVE): Every child in Nigeria deserves access to a library. Yet statistics reveal that fewer than 30% of public schools have a functioning library. This is not merely inconvenient — it is a crisis. Reading is the foundation of all learning; without it, academic progress is impossible. Moreover, research consistently shows that students who read for pleasure outperform their peers in every subject. Governments, school leaders, and parents must act urgently to fund, build, and maintain school libraries. The future of our nation depends on the minds we cultivate today.\n\nQ: What is the main argument of this passage?',['Every Nigerian child deserves access to a school library','Libraries are too expensive to build','Reading for pleasure is not important','Only some students need libraries'],'Every Nigerian child deserves access to a school library',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (persuasive: libraries).\n\nQ: What statistic is used to strengthen the argument?',['Fewer than 30% of public schools have a functioning library','Students who read score 20% higher','Libraries cost 50% more to build than classrooms','40% of students never visit a library'],'Fewer than 30% of public schools have a functioning library',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (persuasive: libraries).\n\nQ: Which technique is used in: "This is not merely inconvenient — it is a crisis."',['Exaggeration/hyperbole for emphasis','A rhetorical question','A rule of three','A metaphor'],'Exaggeration/hyperbole for emphasis',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (persuasive: libraries).\n\nQ: Who does the author say must act to fund libraries?',['Governments, school leaders, and parents','Only the government','Only parents','Only school leaders'],'Governments, school leaders, and parents',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (persuasive: libraries).\n\nQ: What technique is used in: "The future of our nation depends on the minds we cultivate today"?',['Appeal to the future / consequences','A rule of three','A rhetorical question','A statistic'],'Appeal to the future / consequences',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'vocabulary','What does "cultivate" mean?',['to develop and nurture over time','to build quickly','to cut down','to ignore completely'],'to develop and nurture over time',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'vocabulary','What does "consistently" mean?',['always; in a steady, reliable way','occasionally; now and then','rarely; almost never','unpredictably'],'always; in a steady, reliable way',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'grammar','Which of these is a rhetorical question?',['Can we really afford to abandon our children\'s education?','Education is important and must be funded.','Research shows 30% of schools lack libraries.','Governments, schools, and parents must act.'],'Can we really afford to abandon our children\'s education?',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'vocabulary','What does "outperform" mean?',['to do better than others','to perform less well','to perform at the same level','to avoid performing'],'to do better than others',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',6,3,'grammar','Which sentence best uses "direct address"?',['You have the power to change this — and you must use it.','Someone somewhere can help.','Change is possible in some situations.','Libraries can be built by many people.'],'You have the power to change this — and you must use it.',term:2),

