  // Set 1 — comprehension: The Water Cycle
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'comprehension','PASSAGE — The Water Cycle: Water moves continuously through a process called the water cycle. Evaporation occurs when the sun heats water in oceans, rivers, and lakes, turning it into water vapour that rises into the atmosphere. As vapour cools at higher altitudes, it condenses to form clouds. When clouds become heavy with water droplets, precipitation occurs — water falls back as rain, sleet, or snow. This cycle ensures a continuous supply of fresh water and regulates the earth\'s temperature and weather patterns.\n\nQ: What causes evaporation in the water cycle?',['The sun heating water in oceans, rivers, and lakes','Clouds becoming heavy with water droplets','Water falling back to the earth','Wind blowing across the ocean'],'The sun heating water in oceans, rivers, and lakes',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (water cycle).\n\nQ: What does "condenses" mean here?',['Turns from vapour back into tiny water droplets','Rises upward into the atmosphere','Falls as rain, sleet, or snow','Evaporates from the surface'],'Turns from vapour back into tiny water droplets',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (water cycle).\n\nQ: What does "precipitation" mean?',['Water falling back to the earth as rain, sleet, or snow','Water vapour rising into the atmosphere','Water evaporating from the ocean','Clouds forming in the atmosphere'],'Water falling back to the earth as rain, sleet, or snow',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (water cycle).\n\nQ: What are TWO functions of the water cycle?',['Ensures a continuous supply of fresh water and regulates temperature','Causes evaporation only and creates clouds','Produces rain and creates rivers only','Heats the ocean and cools the atmosphere'],'Ensures a continuous supply of fresh water and regulates temperature',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (water cycle).\n\nQ: How many syllables in "precipitation"?',['5','4','6','3'],'5',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'vocabulary','What does "atmosphere" mean?',['the layer of gases surrounding the Earth','the water in the ocean','the clouds in the sky','the surface of the earth'],'the layer of gases surrounding the Earth',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'vocabulary','What does "altitude" mean?',['height above sea level','the temperature of the air','the speed of wind','the depth of water'],'height above sea level',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'vocabulary','What does "regulate" mean?',['to control at a steady level','to increase rapidly','to completely stop','to measure something'],'to control at a steady level',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'vocabulary','What does "continuous" mean?',['without interruption; happening all the time','only happening sometimes','very slow and gradual','happening once only'],'without interruption; happening all the time',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,1,'vocabulary','What does "vapour" mean?',['a substance in gas or fine particle form floating in air','solid frozen water','a body of liquid water','a cloud formation'],'a substance in gas or fine particle form floating in air',term:2),

  // Set 2 — comprehension: Solar Energy in Nigeria
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'comprehension','PASSAGE — Solar Energy in Nigeria: Nigeria is one of the sunniest countries in the world, receiving an average of 5–7 hours of sunshine per day. Solar energy — electricity generated from sunlight using photovoltaic (PV) panels — is increasingly seen as a solution to the country\'s significant energy challenges. Unlike fossil fuels, which release harmful greenhouse gases when burned, solar energy is clean, renewable, and environmentally sustainable. Despite high initial installation costs, many Nigerian households and businesses have begun investing in solar systems, and experts predict that solar energy will play a transformative role in Nigeria\'s development over the next two decades.\n\nQ: How many hours of sunshine does Nigeria receive on average per day?',['5–7 hours','2–3 hours','10–12 hours','8–10 hours'],'5–7 hours',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (solar energy).\n\nQ: What do photovoltaic panels do?',['Convert sunlight into electricity','Absorb rainwater','Power gas generators','Generate wind energy'],'Convert sunlight into electricity',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (solar energy).\n\nQ: Why is solar energy described as better than fossil fuels?',['It is clean, renewable, and does not release greenhouse gases','It is cheaper to install','It produces more electricity','It requires no maintenance'],'It is clean, renewable, and does not release greenhouse gases',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (solar energy).\n\nQ: What challenge does the passage acknowledge?',['High initial installation costs','Lack of sunshine in Nigeria','It produces greenhouse gases','It is not renewable'],'High initial installation costs',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (solar energy).\n\nQ: How many syllables are in "transformative"?',['4','3','5','6'],'4',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'vocabulary','What does "sustainable" mean?',['able to be maintained long-term without causing harm','very expensive to produce','only available short-term','difficult to install'],'able to be maintained long-term without causing harm',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'vocabulary','What does "renewable" mean?',['naturally replenished; not used up permanently','very expensive','difficult to find','non-existent in Nigeria'],'naturally replenished; not used up permanently',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'vocabulary','What does "transformative" mean?',['causing a major, significant change','slightly different from before','difficult to change','not changing at all'],'causing a major, significant change',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'vocabulary','What does "significant" mean in this context?',['large and important','very small','barely noticeable','difficult to measure'],'large and important',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','syllable',8,2,'vocabulary','What does "decade" mean?',['a period of ten years','a period of one hundred years','a period of five years','a period of twenty years'],'a period of ten years',term:2),

  // Set 3 — comprehension: Food Security in West Africa
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'comprehension','PASSAGE — Food Security in West Africa: Food security exists when all people, at all times, have access to sufficient, safe, and nutritious food. West Africa faces significant challenges including rapid population growth, climate change, and inadequate agricultural infrastructure. Despite this, the region is home to a rich diversity of crops including yams, cassava, sorghum, and rice. Innovative farming techniques such as irrigation, crop rotation, and drought-resistant seed varieties are increasingly being adopted. Regional organisations such as ECOWAS play a vital role in coordinating food security policies across member nations.\n\nQ: What is food security?',['When all people always have access to sufficient, safe, and nutritious food','When a country produces enough rice and cassava','When there is no drought in a region','When a government imports sufficient food'],'When all people always have access to sufficient, safe, and nutritious food',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (food security).\n\nQ: Name THREE factors undermining food security in West Africa.',['Population growth, climate change, and inadequate agricultural infrastructure','Drought, flooding, and soil erosion only','Wars, migration, and oil production','Lack of crops, poor soil, and no irrigation'],'Population growth, climate change, and inadequate agricultural infrastructure',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (food security).\n\nQ: What does "innovative" mean here?',['New and creative; introducing better methods','Old-fashioned and traditional','Expensive and impractical','Imported from outside the region'],'New and creative; introducing better methods',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (food security).\n\nQ: What role does ECOWAS play?',['It coordinates food security policies across member nations','It directly farms crops across West Africa','It imports food from outside Africa','It controls the price of food in all markets'],'It coordinates food security policies across member nations',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (food security).\n\nQ: Which word uses the prefix meaning "not" + "adequate"?',['inadequate','innovative','infrastructure','irrigation'],'inadequate',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'vocabulary','What does "infrastructure" mean?',['the basic systems and structures needed for a society to function','a type of farming technique','a kind of food variety','a type of irrigation system'],'the basic systems and structures needed for a society to function',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'vocabulary','What does "nutritious" mean?',['containing substances good for health and growth','very expensive to produce','difficult to find','only available in large quantities'],'containing substances good for health and growth',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'vocabulary','What does "drought-resistant" mean?',['able to survive with very little water','needing a large amount of water','growing only in wet climates','unable to survive in dry conditions'],'able to survive with very little water',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'vocabulary','What does "undermining" mean?',['gradually weakening or damaging something','strongly supporting something','quickly building something up','completely replacing something'],'gradually weakening or damaging something',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',8,3,'vocabulary','What does "diversity" mean?',['a variety or range of different things','the same type of thing repeated','only one kind of thing','a lack of options'],'a variety or range of different things',term:2),

