  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,2,'grammar','Which sentence uses passive voice correctly in a report?',['It has been found that deforestation contributes to climate change.','We found that deforestation contributes to climate change.','I found that deforestation contributes to climate change.','They found out that deforestation is contributing.'],'It has been found that deforestation contributes to climate change.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',9,2,'vocabulary','What does "significant" mean in a report context?',['large enough to be important; noteworthy','very small and minor','slightly interesting but not important','completely unknown'],'large enough to be important; noteworthy',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,2,'grammar','What is a "recommendation" in a report?',['A suggestion for what should be done based on the findings','A summary of what was found','An introduction to the topic','A list of vocabulary terms'],'A suggestion for what should be done based on the findings',term:2),

  // Set 3 — comprehension: sample report
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'comprehension','PASSAGE — Sample Report (extract): The Impact of Technology on Education\n\nIntroduction: Technology has fundamentally transformed the way students learn and teachers teach. Over the past decade, digital tools such as tablets, laptops, and online learning platforms have become increasingly prevalent.\n\nKey Benefits: Research consistently demonstrates that interactive technology improves student engagement. According to a 2022 UNESCO report, schools that integrated digital tools saw a 35% improvement in student outcomes. Furthermore, technology enables personalised learning.\n\nChallenges: Nevertheless, significant challenges remain. Access to reliable electricity and internet is unequal, particularly in rural areas. Without addressing this infrastructure gap, the benefits will not be equitably distributed.\n\nQ: What is the main topic of this report?',['The impact of technology on education','The history of schools in Nigeria','How to use tablets in a classroom','The challenges of internet connectivity only'],'The impact of technology on education',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'comprehension','Refer to the report above (technology and education).\n\nQ: What statistic is cited to support the benefits?',['Schools using digital tools saw a 35% improvement in student outcomes','Technology reduces costs by 20%','Students using tablets score 50% higher','75% of students prefer online learning'],'Schools using digital tools saw a 35% improvement in student outcomes',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'comprehension','Refer to the report above (technology and education).\n\nQ: What major challenge is identified?',['Unequal access to electricity and internet in rural areas','The high cost of tablets','Teachers not knowing how to use technology','Students spending too much time online'],'Unequal access to electricity and internet in rural areas',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'comprehension','Refer to the report above (technology and education).\n\nQ: Which transition word introduces the challenges section?',['Nevertheless','Furthermore','According to','In conclusion'],'Nevertheless',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'comprehension','Refer to the report above (technology and education).\n\nQ: What does "equitably distributed" mean in the final sentence?',['Shared fairly so everyone benefits equally','Distributed only to wealthy schools','Distributed as quickly as possible','Shared in order of school size'],'Shared fairly so everyone benefits equally',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'vocabulary','What does "prevalent" mean?',['widespread; commonly found','extremely rare','only found in cities','very expensive'],'widespread; commonly found',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'vocabulary','What does "integrated" mean in the report?',['combined and included as part of a whole','separated from the main system','used only once','tested before use'],'combined and included as part of a whole',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'grammar','Which word in the report is domain-specific to education technology?',['platforms','transformation','challenges','distribution'],'platforms',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',9,3,'vocabulary','What does "personalised" mean?',['designed or adapted for a specific individual','shared equally with everyone','very formal and official','done without preparation'],'designed or adapted for a specific individual',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',9,3,'grammar','Which sentence from the report uses passive voice?',['Schools that integrated digital tools saw a 35% improvement.','Research consistently demonstrates that technology improves engagement.','Technology has fundamentally transformed the way students learn.','Students can progress at their own pace.'],'Schools that integrated digital tools saw a 35% improvement.',term:2),

