  // Set 3 — comprehension: editing for homophones
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'comprehension','PASSAGE — Editing for Homophones: One of the most common errors in written English is confusing homophones — words that sound identical but differ in meaning. Consider: "complement/compliment", "desert/dessert", "eminent/imminent", and "elicit/illicit". When proofreading, it is not enough to rely on spell-checkers, because a spell-checker will not flag "dessert" if you write "The Sahara is a vast dessert." The word is spelled correctly — it is just the wrong word. Careful re-reading with attention to meaning is the only reliable way to catch these errors.\n\nQ: Why is a spell-checker unreliable for homophone errors?',['It will not flag a correctly-spelled but wrongly-used word','It cannot recognise any English words','Homophones are too rare to be a concern','Spell-checkers always correct every error'],'It will not flag a correctly-spelled but wrongly-used word',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (editing for homophones).\n\nQ: What example of a spell-checker miss does the passage give?',['"The Sahara is a vast dessert" (should be "desert")','Using "their" instead of "there"','Using "two" instead of "to"','Using "its" instead of "it\'s"'],'"The Sahara is a vast dessert" (should be "desert")',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (editing for homophones).\n\nQ: What is the only reliable way to catch homophone errors?',['Careful re-reading with attention to meaning','Using a spell-checker','Asking a friend to proofread','Using a grammar checker'],'Careful re-reading with attention to meaning',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (editing for homophones).\n\nQ: Which four homophone pairs are listed?',['complement/compliment, desert/dessert, eminent/imminent, elicit/illicit','affect/effect, principle/principal, counsel/council, there/their','past/passed, flair/flare, accept/except, desert/dessert','elicit/illicit, flair/flare, accept/except, eminent/imminent'],'complement/compliment, desert/dessert, eminent/imminent, elicit/illicit',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (editing for homophones).\n\nQ: What does "proofreading" mean?',['Carefully reading a text to find and correct errors','Writing a first draft','Using a spell-checker to correct spelling','Reading a text aloud to an audience'],'Carefully reading a text to find and correct errors',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'grammar','Choose the correct word: "The arrival of the storm was ___; dark clouds had already gathered."',['imminent','eminent','continent','elegant'],'imminent',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'grammar','Choose the correct word: "The school ___ all applications by the 30th of November."',['accepted','excepted','effected','elicited'],'accepted',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'vocabulary','Which sentence contains a homophone error?',['He past the library on his way to school.','She passed all her examinations with distinction.','The past few weeks have been challenging.','She accepted the award graciously.'],'He past the library on his way to school.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',10,3,'grammar','Choose the correct word: "He tried to ___ an honest answer from the witness."',['elicit','illicit','eminent','accept'],'elicit',term:2),
