  // Set 1
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'grammar','Which sentence presents an argument most persuasively?',['Technology in schools is essential because it prepares students for a digital future and significantly improves engagement.','Technology in schools is good because students like it.','I think technology is important and should be in schools.','Technology might be nice in schools sometimes.'],'Technology in schools is essential because it prepares students for a digital future and significantly improves engagement.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'grammar','Which sentence politely challenges an opposing point in a debate?',['While I understand your perspective, the evidence suggests otherwise.','You are completely wrong about this.','That point makes no sense at all.','I disagree and your point is bad.'],'While I understand your perspective, the evidence suggests otherwise.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'vocabulary','What does "refute" mean in a debate?',['to prove a point wrong with evidence','to agree with an argument','to repeat an argument','to present a new point'],'to prove a point wrong with evidence',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'vocabulary','What does "concede" mean in a debate?',['to admit that a point made by the other side is valid','to win the argument','to repeat your own point more forcefully','to refuse to answer'],'to admit that a point made by the other side is valid',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'grammar','Which phrase best introduces a counter-argument?',['One might argue that..., however,...','Also the other side says...','But the opponents think...','On the other side there is a point...'],'One might argue that..., however,...',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'vocabulary','What does "proposition" mean in a debate?',['the side arguing in favour of the motion','the side arguing against the motion','the judge of the debate','the topic being discussed'],'the side arguing in favour of the motion',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'vocabulary','What does "opposition" mean in a debate?',['the side arguing against the motion','the side arguing in favour','the audience','the topic being debated'],'the side arguing against the motion',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'grammar','Which is the most effective way to conclude a debate argument?',['In conclusion, the evidence overwhelmingly supports our position that...','In conclusion, we are right and they are wrong.','So basically we have made our points.','To end, our side has said many things.'],'In conclusion, the evidence overwhelmingly supports our position that...',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'vocabulary','What does "substantiate" mean?',['to provide evidence that proves a claim','to repeat a claim loudly','to disprove a claim','to avoid making a claim'],'to provide evidence that proves a claim',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,1,'grammar','Which rhetorical device is used: "If we ban school uniforms, will students focus more on fashion or on learning?"',['Rhetorical question','Simile','Metaphor','Rule of three'],'Rhetorical question',term:2),

  // Set 2
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'grammar','Which sentence uses evidence most effectively?',['According to a 2021 UNICEF report, students in uniform-wearing schools show 15% higher attendance.','Some people say uniforms help students focus.','I believe uniforms make students more equal.','Uniforms are good because students look the same.'],'According to a 2021 UNICEF report, students in uniform-wearing schools show 15% higher attendance.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'vocabulary','What does "rhetoric" mean?',['the art of using language persuasively','a type of evidence used in debates','a formal debate format','a polite way of agreeing'],'the art of using language persuasively',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'grammar','Which best uses the "rule of three" in a debate?',['Technology transforms learning, builds skills, and opens doors to the future.','Technology is transforming the way students learn things.','Technology has many benefits including learning and skills.','Technology is good for three main reasons.'],'Technology transforms learning, builds skills, and opens doors to the future.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'grammar','Which is the most polite way to disagree?',['With respect, I believe the evidence points to a different conclusion.','You have completely misunderstood the topic.','That argument is entirely wrong.','I strongly disagree with everything you said.'],'With respect, I believe the evidence points to a different conclusion.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'vocabulary','What does "impartial" mean?',['not favouring one side; fair and objective','strongly in favour of one side','strongly against one side','unable to make a decision'],'not favouring one side; fair and objective',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'grammar','Which phrase signals that you are conceding a point?',['I acknowledge that this point has merit, but...','I completely agree with the other side.','There is no merit in the opposition\'s argument.','This point is wrong and I will prove it.'],'I acknowledge that this point has merit, but...',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'vocabulary','What does "credible" mean?',['believable and reliable','unconvincing and weak','based on opinion only','very emotional'],'believable and reliable',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'grammar','Which sentence uses a statistic to strengthen a debate point?',['Studies show that 70% of employers prefer candidates with strong communication skills.','Communication skills are very important for employment.','Most employers want people who can communicate well.','I think communication skills are one of the most important things.'],'Studies show that 70% of employers prefer candidates with strong communication skills.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'vocabulary','What does "coherent" mean?',['logical and well-structured; easy to follow','very loud and forceful','full of emotion','difficult to understand'],'logical and well-structured; easy to follow',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,2,'grammar','Which is the best opening for a debate speech?',['Today, we stand before you to argue that access to quality education is not a privilege — it is a fundamental right.','Today I will talk about why education is important.','In this debate, our side will say education is a right.','My team believes education is important and we will explain.'],'Today, we stand before you to argue that access to quality education is not a privilege — it is a fundamental right.',term:2),

  // Set 3 — comprehension: debate excerpt
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'comprehension','PASSAGE (DEBATE EXCERPT — FOR SCHOOL UNIFORMS): "Good afternoon. We, the proposition, firmly believe that school uniforms should remain compulsory in Nigerian schools. The evidence is clear: uniformity reduces economic inequality, prevents distractions caused by clothing choices, and creates a sense of belonging and identity. According to research by the University of Lagos, schools with mandatory uniforms report 20% fewer disciplinary incidents. Our opponents may argue that uniforms restrict individual expression — and while we concede that self-expression has value, it must be balanced against the broader needs of an equitable learning environment."\n\nQ: What is the position of the speaker?',['The proposition — arguing in favour of school uniforms','The opposition — arguing against school uniforms','The chair of the debate','A neutral observer'],'The proposition — arguing in favour of school uniforms',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (debate excerpt).\n\nQ: What evidence does the speaker use?',['Research showing schools with uniforms have 20% fewer disciplinary incidents','A personal opinion that uniforms look better','A statistic about the cost of school uniforms','A quote from a student who likes uniforms'],'Research showing schools with uniforms have 20% fewer disciplinary incidents',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (debate excerpt).\n\nQ: What counter-argument does the speaker acknowledge?',['That uniforms restrict individual self-expression','That uniforms are too expensive for poor families','That uniforms cause more disciplinary problems','That uniforms are not worn in other countries'],'That uniforms restrict individual self-expression',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (debate excerpt).\n\nQ: The speaker says "we concede that self-expression has value." What does "concede" mean?',['The speaker admits the opposing point has some truth','The speaker is changing their position entirely','The speaker is refusing to answer','The speaker is repeating their own argument'],'The speaker admits the opposing point has some truth',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (debate excerpt).\n\nQ: Which technique is used in: "uniformity reduces economic inequality... prevents distractions... and creates a sense of belonging"?',['Rule of three','Rhetorical question','Simile','Direct address'],'Rule of three',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'vocabulary','What does "compulsory" mean?',['required by rules or law; mandatory','optional and voluntary','recommended but not required','discouraged'],'required by rules or law; mandatory',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'vocabulary','What does "equitable" mean?',['fair and equal for everyone','favouring one group only','very formal and official','difficult to achieve'],'fair and equal for everyone',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'grammar','Which debate opening uses "direct address" effectively?',['Imagine a school where every student feels equal, confident, and ready to learn.','In this debate we will argue about school uniforms.','Our team believes school uniforms are a good idea.','School uniforms have many benefits which we will discuss.'],'Imagine a school where every student feels equal, confident, and ready to learn.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'vocabulary','What does "disciplinary" mean?',['relating to maintaining rules and order','relating to academic results','relating to school uniforms','relating to classroom furniture'],'relating to maintaining rules and order',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',12,3,'grammar','Which phrase could the opposition use to politely refute the cited statistic?',['While the statistic is notable, other factors may also explain the improvement in discipline.','The statistic is completely false and irrelevant.','No research supports school uniforms.','I disagree with everything the proposition has said.'],'While the statistic is notable, other factors may also explain the improvement in discipline.',term:2),

