  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,1,'vocabulary','The root "tract" means pull. What does "extract" mean?',['to pull out','to build out','to throw out','to carry out'],'to pull out',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,1,'grammar','Which is the correct adjective form of "mystery"?',['mysterious','mysteryous','mystereous','mysterieous'],'mysterious',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,1,'vocabulary','The root "chron" means time. What does "chronological" mean?',['arranged in order of time','relating to living things','relating to the earth','arranged by size'],'arranged in order of time',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,1,'grammar','Which is correct: "perform" + "-ance"?',['performance','performment','performence','performans'],'performance',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',13,1,'vocabulary','Which sentence uses "eminent" correctly?',['An eminent scientist delivered the keynote address.','The storm is eminent; we should go inside.','The eminent flood warning was issued this morning.','She felt the eminent arrival of good news.'],'An eminent scientist delivered the keynote address.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,1,'vocabulary','The root "struct" means build. What does "infrastructure" mean?',['the basic systems and structures needed for a society to function','an act of destruction','a type of instruction','a method of extraction'],'the basic systems and structures needed for a society to function',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,1,'grammar','Which sentence uses a semicolon correctly?',['She studied all night; consequently, she passed with distinction.','She studied all night; but she was tired.','She studied all night; to pass the examination.','She; studied all night and passed.'],'She studied all night; consequently, she passed with distinction.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,1,'grammar','Which is the correct adjective form of "courage"?',['courageous','couragious','couragoues','courageuous'],'courageous',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,1,'vocabulary','What does "autobiography" mean? (auto=self, bio=life, graph=write)',['a written account of one\'s own life','a study of the earth','a time-based record','a study of living things'],'a written account of one\'s own life',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',13,1,'vocabulary','What is the difference between "accept" and "except"?',['accept = to receive; except = not including','except = to receive; accept = not including','they mean the same thing','accept is always a noun'],'accept = to receive; except = not including',term:2),

  // Set 2 — mixed grammar + vocabulary
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,2,'vocabulary','The root "ject" means throw. What does "reject" mean?',['to throw back / refuse','to build back','to pull back','to carry back'],'to throw back / refuse',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,2,'grammar','Which is correct: "exist" + "-ence"?',['existence','existment','existance','existens'],'existence',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,2,'vocabulary','The root "geo" means earth. What does "geology" mean?',['the study of rocks and the earth\'s structure','the study of living organisms','the study of time and history','the study of language'],'the study of rocks and the earth\'s structure',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,2,'grammar','What is the formal equivalent of "try"?',['endeavour','have a go at','give it a shot','maybe try to do it'],'endeavour',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','homophone',13,2,'vocabulary','Which sentence uses "complement" correctly?',['The scarf perfectly complements her coat.','She gave him a complement on his new shoes.','He complement the room with flowers.','She complemented him on his great speech.'],'The scarf perfectly complements her coat.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,2,'grammar','Which sentence uses a comma correctly?',['After the ceremony ended, the guests moved to the reception hall.','After the ceremony ended the guests, moved to the reception hall.','After the ceremony, ended the guests moved.','After the ceremony ended the guests moved to the reception, hall.'],'After the ceremony ended, the guests moved to the reception hall.',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,2,'vocabulary','What does "biodiversity" mean?',['the variety of living organisms in an area','the variety of rocks in an area','the range of time periods studied','the range of geographical features'],'the variety of living organisms in an area',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,2,'grammar','Which is the correct noun form of "achieve"?',['achievement','achieveance','achievence','achiev'],'achievement',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,2,'vocabulary','What does "obstruct" mean?',['to block or get in the way of something','to build something quickly','to pull something apart','to throw something away'],'to block or get in the way of something',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,2,'grammar','Which word is the formal equivalent of "a lot of"?',['numerous','loads of','tons of','heaps of'],'numerous',term:2),

  // Set 3 — comprehension: cumulative end-of-term passage
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,3,'comprehension','PASSAGE: Term 2 at Brightfield Academy covered a broad range of language skills. Students explored new Latin roots — tract (pull), struct (build), and ject (throw) — and Greek roots including chron (time), geo (earth), and bio (life). They studied complex suffixes such as -ous, -ment, -ance, and -ence, which helped them expand their vocabulary significantly. Persuasive writing techniques, formal versus informal register, and report writing were all practised. Students also refined their punctuation skills, particularly the use of commas and semicolons. The term ended with a lively debate on whether mobile phones should be allowed in schools.\n\nQ: Which three Latin roots were studied this term?',['tract, struct, ject','port, rupt, dict','vis, aud, scrib','graph, phon, scope'],'tract, struct, ject',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (Term 2 review).\n\nQ: Which three Greek roots were studied?',['chron, geo, bio','graph, phon, scope','port, rupt, dict','tract, struct, ject'],'chron, geo, bio',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (Term 2 review).\n\nQ: Which suffixes are mentioned?',['-ous, -ment, -ance, -ence','-ing, -ed, -er, -est','-tion, -sion, -cion, -ible','-ful, -less, -ly, -ness'],'-ous, -ment, -ance, -ence',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','suffix',13,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (Term 2 review).\n\nQ: What punctuation skills were refined?',['The use of commas and semicolons','Full stops and question marks only','Apostrophes and colons','Brackets and dashes'],  'The use of commas and semicolons',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,3,'comprehension','Refer to the passage above (Term 2 review).\n\nQ: What was the debate topic at the end of term?',['Whether mobile phones should be allowed in schools','Whether school uniforms should be compulsory','Whether students should have more homework','Whether the school day should be longer'],'Whether mobile phones should be allowed in schools',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,3,'vocabulary','What does "refined" mean in the passage?',['improved and made more precise','made rougher','completely changed','removed entirely'],'improved and made more precise',term:2),
  _qu2('upper','prefix',13,3,'grammar','Which sentence uses "construct" correctly?',['The students will construct a model of the solar system.','The students will extract a model of the solar system.','The students will inject a model of the solar system.','The students will distract a model of the solar system.'],'The students will construct a model of the solar system.',term:2),
